flowRoot.flowPara: It is produced by the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland. It is structurally very similar to the opioids (opium, morphine, heroin, etc.) and has similar functions: Inhibitory, it is involved in pain reduction and pleasure, and the opioid drugs work by attaching to endorphin's receptor sites. It is also the neurotransmitter that allows animals to hibernate. It slows heart-rate, respiration, and metabolism in general. Endorphins are suspected to play a role in depersonalization disorder.
